@atomiks Ariakit has a good example on what I believe @brunobely wants. https://ariakit.org/examples/menu-nested-combobox

It composes their Menu component with a Combobox component. 

<img width="627" height="532" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/253d62de-b0a8-44e7-9fba-9850c71bcd5a" />

I built something similar using `Menu` + `Autocomplete` [Preview here](https://apsara-ikqpeob98-raystack.vercel.app/docs/components/menu#autocomplete)

I had to manually trigger focus events to make it work. There are still a few rough edges, but overall it works well.

@atomiks From a DX point of view, it might be worth adding built-in support for this in Menu, even tho it might not be the cleanest. It would be very helpful if this feature was supported natively.

Jumping in with an example that uses a Combobox within DropdownContent (SubContent) - for cases where you need memorable selections and other Combobox goodies and therefore can't use Autocomplete.

Check out a quick [Preview](https://stackblitz.com/edit/vitejs-vite-ppbxpzec?file=src%2FApp.tsx)

```tsx
            <DropdownMenuSub loopFocus>
              <DropdownMenuSubTrigger delay={0}>
                {selectedState?.label || "Select State"}
              </DropdownMenuSubTrigger>

              <DropdownMenuSubContent
                //  role="dialog" overrides the default role="menu" to allow non-menu-item children (combobox) without violating ARIA content model
                role="dialog"
                className="w-52"
                // Focus the input on hover so combobox keyboard bindings stay responsive
                onPointerEnter={focusComboboxInput}
              >
                <StateCombobox
                  // needed to allow correct keyboard navigation and enter key selection
                  open
                  inline
                  value={selectedState?.value || ""}
                  onValueChange={(currentValue, eventDetails) => {
                    onStateChange(currentValue?.value);
                    // Prevents popup-like close behavior so filtering stays responsive
                    // during inline combobox rendering
                    eventDetails.cancel();
                  }}
                  countryCode={selectedCountry?.value as CountryCode}
                >
                  <ComboboxInput
                    autoFocus
                    onKeyDown={(e) => {
                      // Allow Escape, ArrowLeft (at pos 0), and Tab to bubble up to
                      // the menu for submenu close / back-navigation / focus management.
                      // Block everything else so menu's typeahead and list navigation
                      // don't intercept combobox keystrokes.
                      if (e.key === "Escape") return;
                      if (
                        e.key === "ArrowLeft" &&
                        e.currentTarget.selectionStart === 0
                      )
                        return;
                      if (e.key === "Tab") return;
                      e.stopPropagation();
                    }}
                    placeholder="Search State"
                  />

                  <ComboboxEmpty>No options available.</ComboboxEmpty>

                  <StateComboboxList />
                </StateCombobox>
              </DropdownMenuSubContent>
            </DropdownMenuSub>
```
